[Farmers are directed above to clinical signs which are not to be expected anyway during the non-vector season. What European farmers should be watching for(and hopefully, not see) in the near future is the outcome of infection which could have taken place last summer/fall, namely the possible appearance of malformations in progeny of imported ruminants. These, however, are not likely to be infective. -Mod. AS].

